CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 11, 1956, pg. 1, reads: "Dogged Determination - Like the look on the dog's face, the determination of Mrs. Martha E. Moore to gain the First Legislative District's General Assembly post is rugged. Mrs. Moore and her family pet, Baron Swabisch Gunund, took over her petition blanks for the Republican primary. She is endorsed by the Fifth Ward GOP committee. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Martha E. Moore wearing knitted collar and posed with German Boxer dog "Baron Swabisch Gunund," in her home at 814 Cherokee Street, Schenley Heights
